SUMMARY:Resonance
DESCRIPTION:The veena from Ayodhya meets the bansuri from a Mumbai gurukul. The mridangam of a dynasty meets the tabla of the first generation. \nSome raagas on this programme belong to both Indian classical traditions\, the same soul unfolding differently in each. Others belong exclusively to one. In the moments of improvisation\, there are no boundaries between instrument and artist\, North and South. \nAn evening of Carnatic and Hindustani music\, in conversation. Samvad.  \nSupported by:\n \n
URL:https://bangaloreinternationalcentre.org/event/resonance/
LOCATION:Bangalore International Centre\, 7\, 4th Main Road\, Domlur II Stage\, Bangalore\, Karnataka\, 560071\, India
CATEGORIES:Music,Performing Arts
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://bangaloreinternationalcentre.org/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Thumbnail_RN-1.jpg
END:VEVENT
