SUMMARY:Mothers of Daughters
DESCRIPTION:Idolised\, worshipped\, immortalised. A mother is asked to be everything while making it look effortless. \nAlas\, a mother is also a daughter. In the face of her humanity\, we know not what to do. \nMeyeder Mayera is a Bangla anthology of mothers written by their daughters. Not the idea of a mother\, but the women themselves. Arundhati Ghosh joins four contributors to the book in a conversation about the legacies it carries\, the relationships that shaped them\, and what it means to truly see the person who raised you. \nThe session will then open for audience questions. \n
URL:https://bangaloreinternationalcentre.org/event/mothers-of-daughters/
LOCATION:Bangalore International Centre\, 7\, 4th Main Road\, Domlur II Stage\, Bangalore\, Karnataka\, 560071\, India
CATEGORIES:Books,Gender
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://bangaloreinternationalcentre.org/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Thumbnail.jpg
