UID:88165-1777203000-1777811400@bangaloreinternationalcentre.org
SUMMARY:The Many Lives of Dance
DESCRIPTION:The Many Lives of Dance is a series of events commemorating World Dance Day\, celebrating the diverse ways in which dance lives\, evolves\, and resonates across contexts. It brings together artists\, scholars\, and practitioners\, to explore how dance moves from being a specialised\, codified practice to a shared\, social\, and deeply personal experience. \nWhile dance is explored as a rigorous system of knowledge\, where technique\, philosophy\, and discipline shape the dancing body\, it is also something that circulates through communities and everyday life through rhythm\, presence\, and collective energy. This series aims to enquire and build the bridge between personal movement languages that become powerful ways of seeing and feeling the world. \nEach event offers a distinct lens\, inviting audiences to engage with dance as a living\, breathing practice that continually transforms with time\, place\, and people. \n\n\n\nDate\nEvent\nArtist\nNature\nTiming\n\n\nApr 26\nPerspectives on Bharata Natyam\nLeela Samson\nLecture Demonstration\n11:30am – 1pm\n\n\nApr 26\nSole to Soul\nJanani Kalasutra\nWorkshop\n4pm – 6pm\n\n\nApr 27\nDāri | The Path\nAvijit Das\, Varsha\, Greeshma and Abhirami\nPerformance\n7pm – 8:30pm\n\n\nApr 28\nThehraav\nMasoom Parmar\nTalk\n6:30pm – 8pm\n\n\nApr 29\nWhat Holds\nGayatri Shetty\nPerformance\n7pm – 8:15pm\n\n\nApr 30\nMaṇṇina Hejje –  Dances of the Soil\nSneha Kappanna\nWorkshop\n6:30pm – 8:30pm\n\n\nMay 1\nIlluminating Dance\nNiranjan Gokhale\nLecture Demonstration\n2pm – 4pm\n\n\nMay 1\nWhy Dance When No One is Watching ?\nDiya Naidu\nLecture Demonstration\n6:30pm – 8:30pm\n\n\nMay 2\nBody as Resource\nPreethi Rajagopalan\nWorkshop\n3pm – 5pm\n\n\nMay 3\nGabbu Kathe\nKeerthi Kumar and Roopa Krishnamurthy\nPerformance\n11:30am – 12:30pm\n\n\n\nMore details will follow shortly. \n
URL:https://bangaloreinternationalcentre.org/event/the-many-lives-of-dance/
LOCATION:Bangalore International Centre\, 7\, 4th Main Road\, Domlur II Stage\, Bangalore\, Karnataka\, 560071\, India
CATEGORIES:Dance,Performing Arts
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://bangaloreinternationalcentre.org/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Thumbnail_TMLOD2.jpg
END:VEVENT
